cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on image-based automated inspection systems for electrical distribution poles. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel two-stage zoom-in detection method and resampling as well as reweighting schemes to adapt the model to the large intra-class variation of major class and balance the contributions to the loss from each class. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also relevant as the paper uses deep neural networks for the proposed automatic inspection framework. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of drone and helicopter inspections for capturing imagery data. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the challenges of analyzing large volumes of imagery data for electrical distribution pole inspections.
